description: A walk up a hill tends to end with this Pal tumbling back down. This causes it to become dizzy and unable to move, making it easy to capture and kill. As a result, this Pal has tumbled down to the very bottom of the food chain itself.
name: Lamball

partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips to the player and becomes a shield. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Fluffy Shield

title: Big Floof

description: At a glance it appears full of confidence, but it is in fact weak and cowardly. Being toyed with by a Cattiva is in many ways the greatest of disgraces.
name: Cattiva

partnerSkill.description: While in team, Cattiva helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: Cat Helper

title: The Cat's Pajamas

description: Extremely weak and far too delicious. It is one of the weakest Pals alongside Lamball. No matter how many are hunted, they just keep appearing.
name: Chikipi

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes lays an Egg when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Egg Layer

title: Plump & Juicy

description: Intelligent as a five to seven-year-old human child. It makes a wonderful partner, but there have been more than a few cases where they've killed their master after learning to use weapons.
name: Lifmunk

partnerSkill.description: When activated, leaps onto the player's head and uses a submachine gun to follows up player attacks.
partnerSkill.name: Lifmunk Recoil

title: Coward of the Steppe

description: It is unskilled at controlling fire from the moment it is born and tends to choke on the flames it breathes unintentionally. Foxparks sneezes are one of the leading causes of forest fires.
name: Foxparks

partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips to the player and transforms into a flamethrower.
partnerSkill.name: Huggy Fire

title: Revealer of Paths

description: Using its own body water, this Pal can create waves anywhere. It body surfs when in a hurry, but the resulting speed often ends in a fatal collision.
name: Fuack

partnerSkill.description: When activated, Fuack body surfs towards an enemy and slams into them.
partnerSkill.name: Surfing Slam

title: Rowdy Wave Ripper

description: During the dry season, this Pal is always on the verge of blowing a fuse. Sparks can fly with even the slightest provocation, even amongst allies.
name: Sparkit

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Electric Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Static Electricity

title: Livewire Tabby

description: Long ago, this Pal used long objects like tree branches as weapons. After coming into contact with humans, however, it found something slightly more effective: guns.
name: Tanzee

partnerSkill.description: When activated, Tanzee will mercilessly fire an assault rifle at nearby enemies.
partnerSkill.name: Cheery Rifle

title: Dexterous Primate

description: Wild Rooby surprisingly never get sick. Eating one piece of charcoal a day, made by burning a branch, is the secret to its eternal health.
name: Rooby

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Fire Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Tiny Spark

title: Chief of the Herd

description: The feathers of this Pal have all but disappeared, but sadly, its desire to fly has remained as strong as ever. Even now, it tries to fly again in any way it can.
name: Pengullet

partnerSkill.description: When activated, the player equips a Rocket Launcher and fires Pengullet as ammunition. Pengullet explodes on contact and is incapacitated.
partnerSkill.name: Pengullet Cannon

title: Ate Too Much

description: Surprisingly, it is unrelated to Pengullet. Ever wanting to be the center of attention, this Pal will strut its stuff for any onlookers.
name: Penking

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Fire Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Brave Sailor

title: Pioneer of the Frozen Sea

description: Releases the electricity stored in its body when under attack, producing a shock that can be over 10 million volts. If thrown, it can even be more lethal than any conventional heavy weaponry.
name: Jolthog

partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips Jolthog to the player's hand. When thrown at an enemy, causes an electrical explosion upon impact.
partnerSkill.name: Jolt Bomb

title: Don't Touch!

description: It releases the cold air stored in its body when under attack. The frigid blast it radiates is cold enough to freeze the surrounding air and easily pierces through any attacker's body.
name: Jolthog Cryst

partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips Jolthog Cryst to the player's hand. When thrown at an enemy, causes an icy explosion upon impact.
partnerSkill.name: Cold Bomb

title: Watch Your Feet!

description: A strange Pal with a body resembling tree sap. It gradually loses strength if it has nothing to cover its body with, eventually rotting away.
name: Gumoss

partnerSkill.description: While in team, improves efficiency of cutting trees.
partnerSkill.name: Logging Assistance

title: Suddenly Transformed

description: The idol of Palpagos Island. If you bully a Vixy, you best be prepared to become enemies with the whole world.
name: Vixy

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up items from the ground when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Dig Here!

title: Star of the Steppe

description: Often lost in thought, it sometimes finds it difficult to sleep. |I think, therefore I am.|
name: Hoocrates

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Dark Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Dark Knowledge

title: Purveyor of Wisdom

description: Large amounts of water pour from what is thought to be its nose, though some say that it is, in fact, just snot. This has sparked a fierce debate among Pal scholars.
name: Teafant

partnerSkill.description: When activated, spouts mysterious water that soothes wounds and restores the player's Health.
partnerSkill.name: Soothing Shower

title: Adorable Watering Can

description: It has few friends because of the perpetually grouchy look on its face, but it is in fact kindhearted. Some have seen it feeding Vixywho have strayed from their pack.
name: Depresso

partnerSkill.description: When activated, Depresso drinks a massive amount of energy drinks, causing its movement speed to increase.
partnerSkill.name: Caffeine Inoculation

title: Several Sleepless Nights Later

description: Compared to Lamball, it has finer wool and a temperament more suited for domestication. However, it has historically always been kept as a pet. Cuteness is considered a virtue.
name: Cremis

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Neutral Pals. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Fluffy Wool

title: Darling Furball

description: It puts those it is interested in to sleep and shows them an endless stream of happy dreams. Those who fall under its spell are never to wake until death takes them.
name: Daedream

partnerSkill.description: While in team, appears near the player. Follows up player attacks with magic bullets.
partnerSkill.name: Dream Chaser

title: Dream Eater

description: Being an extremely aggressive Pal, it often picks fights before gauging its opponents' strength. Though small, its powerful charge can even send boulders flying.
name: Rushoar

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Increases efficiency of destroying boulders while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Hard Head

title: Woodland Ruffian

description: If you find Nox hair in your bedding, you should leave it where it lays and leave immediately. Picking it up is a one-way-ticket to a never ending night.
name: Nox

partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, applies Dark damage to the player's attacks.
partnerSkill.name: Kuudere

title: Dusken Aristocrat

description: Its large claws boast of diamond-like hardness. However, sharpening these claws consumes most of its energy, leading it to sometimes spending entire days doing nothing else.
name: Fuddler

partnerSkill.description: When activated, generates subtle vibrations to detect nearby ore.
partnerSkill.name: Ore Detector

title: Underground Explorer

description: It wraps itself around an enemy's head, sucking out their insides. Pal mummies are occasionally found, but these are in fact Killamari victims.
name: Killamari

partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Can float for long periods of time while gliding.
partnerSkill.name: Fried Squid

title: Emotionless

description: Its hard tail does not deteriorate even when cut off. Some believed these severed tails to be good luck, but for the innumerable Mau who were poached as a result, they were anything but.
name: Mau

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up Gold Coin when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Gold Digger

title: Noble Glimmer

description: Its crystalline tail is beautiful, but shatters when this Pal dies. Some believe it is good luck to raise one, so Mau Cryst in captivity are treated with great care.
name: Mau Cryst

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up Gold Coin when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Gold Digger

title: Serene Glimmer

description: Riding the wind, this Pal travels where it pleases. Should it find a partner along the way, the encounter will mark its journey's end.
name: Celaray

partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Allows you to move quickly for long periods of time while gliding with this Pal.
partnerSkill.name: Zephyr Glider

title: Soaring Skyfish

description: Long ago Direhowl would hunt alongside humans but over the years this bond faded.
name: Direhowl

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Moves slightly faster than most mounts.
partnerSkill.name: Direhowl Rider

title: Hunter of the Steppe

description: A frightening Pal that produces exploding eggs. It often fires these eggs from its rear end as a form of defense, but when spent, the Pal itself explodes.
name: Tocotoco

partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips to the player and transforms into an egg launcher.
partnerSkill.name: Eggbomb Launcher

title: Boom or Bust

description: It prefers places that have an abundance of vegetation, but hay fever has apparently become a problem for Flopie as of late.
name: Flopie

partnerSkill.description: While in team, appears near the player. Automatically picks up nearby items.
partnerSkill.name: Helper Bunny

title: Star of the Flower Beds

description: Milk pours from this Pal like water from an open faucet, regardless of its gender. It's truly a mystery of life, although this mystery may be better left unsolved.
name: Mozzarina

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes produces Milk when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Milk Maker

title: Grade A Beef

description: This prickly Pal's thorns are highly poisonous. It is friendly with Cinnamoth and only smiles while a Cinnamoth is drinking its nectar.
name: Bristla

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Grass Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Princess Gaze

title: Thorny Rose

description: Long ago, it was a large and powerful aquatic Pal. As food became scarce it evolved to live on land. Since walking requires much energy, it gradually became smaller and is now a small and puny Pal.
name: Gobfin

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Aqua Gun. While in team, increases player's attack power.
partnerSkill.name: Angry Shark

title: Sea Thug

description: Once upon a time, it was a giant and powerful aquatic Pal. However, with the dwindling availability of food, it ventured onto land. As a consequence of burning many calories to walk, it astonishingly awakened its power to control fire!
name: Gobfin Ignis

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Spirit Fire. While in team, increases player's attack power.
partnerSkill.name: Angry Shark

title: Volcano Thug

description: Its gigantic arms can rip apart even iron. As a particularly cruel form of execution, serious criminals would be strung up in a public square, and a Hangyu would tear the skin right from their bones.
name: Hangyu

partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Carries the player up high while gliding.
partnerSkill.name: Flying Trapeze

title: Bringer of Luck

description: Its gigantic arms can tear through blocks of ice. There were times when great sinners were tied in the town square and had their hair torn out by Hangyu Cryst as a brutal form of public humiliation.
name: Hangyu Cryst

partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Carries the player up high while gliding.
partnerSkill.name: Winter Trapeze

title: Glacial Harbinger

description: A Pal so powerful it's hard to believe. In one experiment, this Pal tore through 3,000 sheets of paper at once! It's only by some miracle that this Pal isn't a meat-eater.
name: Mossanda

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a grenade launcher while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Grenadier Panda

title: Guardian of the Forest

description: A Pal whose power is truly shocking. By altering the electrical currents in its body, this Pal's been able to overload its own strength. When it comes to sheer power, this Pal may be top of the list.
name: Mossanda Lux

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a grenade launcher while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Grenadier Panda

title: Inheritor of the Storm

description: Its entire body is 18,000 times sweeter than sugar. Carnivorous Pals lured by its scent will find themselves overwhelmed by sweetness and even pass out should they take a bite of this Pal.
name: Woolipop

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Cotton Candy when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Candy Pop

title: Giant Cotton Candy

description: The shrub on this Pal's back produces berries as long as it is properly fed. It offers these berries to potential mates, and if the flavor is to their liking, romance blossoms.
name: Caprity

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Red Berries from its back when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Berry Picker

title: Walking Farm

description: Don't be fooled by this Pal's fluffy appearance. A hypersonic kick from one of its long legs may send you flying to the other side of the world.
name: Melpaca

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Pacapaca Wool

title: Pompous Shanks

description: The one who possesses the most impressive antlers becomes the leader of the herd. If their antlers are broken, they become depressed and leave the herd never to be seen again.
name: Eikthyrdeer

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can perform a double jump while mounted. Increases efficiency of cutting trees.
partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Forest

title: Protector of the Herd

description: The individual with the hardest horns becomes the leader. Once the horns are lost, so too is its leadership status. It leaves the herd amidst farewell glances and quietly returns to the earth.
name: Eikthyrdeer Terra

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can perform a double jump while mounted. Increases efficiency of cutting trees.
partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Golden Forest

title: Antlers of Gold

description: It carries newborn Pals to its nest and raises them as a surrogate parent. Once the baby Pal has fattened up, it hunts them.
name: Nitewing

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount.
partnerSkill.name: Travel Companion

title: Wings of the Firmament

description: A Pal who's never without a bright smile. Occasionally, it gets its tentacles tied up in knots by Cattiva's pranks. During those moments, its expression changes into something altogether demonic.
name: Ribbuny

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Neutral Pals. While at a base, increases work efficiency if working at Weapon Workbench.
partnerSkill.name: Skilled Fingers

title: Heart-melting Smile

description: In the dark of night, this Pal snatches prey to bring back to its territory. What happens to those poor souls afterwards isn't too hard to imagine.
name: Incineram

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Hellfire Claw.
partnerSkill.name: Flameclaw Hunter

title: Hyena of the Wild

description: It specifically targets baby pals, taking them back to its territory. One can only imagine the profound despair of the parent Pal, whose child has been taken away.
name: Incineram Noct

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Hellfire Claw.
partnerSkill.name: Darkclaw Hunter

title: Hyena of the Darkest Night

description: Sniffing its scales produces a feeling of unparalleled euphoria. There was some effort to further regulate this byproduct, but the Free Pal Alliance have vehemently opposed these measures, putting a stop to them.
name: Cinnamoth

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with Poison Fog.
partnerSkill.name: Mysterious Scales

title: Butterfly Promenade

description: In ancient times, carnivorous Pals pursued them relentlessly. The absurd fury in the cries of Arsox transformed into a raging inferno, which has been passed on to this day.
name: Arsox

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Keeps the rider warm in cold environments.
partnerSkill.name: Warm Body

title: Blazing Brute

description: When too relaxed, its reaction time drastically declines. Even if it were sliced from head to tail, it probably wouldn't even realize that it should be dead until the next morning.
name: Dumud

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Ground Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Soil Improver

title: Perpetual Procrastinator

description: Long ago it freely soared the skies. After losing a contest with Galeclaw, it abandoned the skies, and now lives a secretive life in the dark of night.
name: Cawgnito

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Phantom Peck.
partnerSkill.name: Telepeck

title: Shadow-cloaked Schemer

description: A Pal that always takes great care to maintain a stylish stance. Always on the hunt for the coolest poses, if given a mirror it will spend all day posing in front of it.
name: Leezpunk

partnerSkill.description: When activated, utilizes its sixth sense to detect nearby dungeons.
partnerSkill.name: Sixth Sense

title: Self-proclaimed Genius

description: A Pal that has an unusual obsession with their standing posture. Always in search of the hottest pose, this Pal's owner is constantly presented with fervent stances.
name: Leezpunk Ignis

partnerSkill.description: When activated, utilizes its sixth sense to detect nearby dungeons.
partnerSkill.name: Sixth Sense

title: Self-proclaimed Fashionista

description: The horns on its head grow under the moonlight. It doesn't hate the sun, but its horns itch when sunlight hits them.
name: Loupmoon

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Jumping Claw.
partnerSkill.name: Claws Glistening in the Dark

title: Enraptured by Moonlight

description: A Pal that can easily take flight even while grasping a human. It is, however, prone to letting go when tired, which has led to the sudden demise of more than a few souls.
name: Galeclaw

partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Allows you to fire a gun while gliding with this Pal.
partnerSkill.name: Galeclaw Rider

title: Proud Courier

description: A pal that is very similar to humans who hunt and live in the forests. It may prove to be a key for understanding what Pals are and how they diverged from humans so long ago.
name: Robinquill

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, allows you to deal more damage to weak points.
partnerSkill.name: Hawk Eye

title: Archer of the Forest

description: A Pal that lives a hunting life in rocky areas and is very close to humans. When Robinquill Terra bones are found in ruins, there are always human bones found nearby as well.
name: Robinquill Terra

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, allows you to deal more damage to weak points.
partnerSkill.name: Hawk Eye

title: Archer of the Sands

description: It beats the ground rhythmically to communicate with its comrades. The meaning of each rhythm differs by troop, but the distinction between them is still largely unknown.
name: Gorirat

partnerSkill.description: When activated, unleashes a primal fury that increases Gorirat's attack power.
partnerSkill.name: Full-power Gorilla Mode

title: Jungle Punk

description: A servant that pledges loyalty to Elizabee. Any that cause harm to the queen are immediately expelled from the hive. It will gladly give its life to protect its queen.
name: Beegarde

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Honey when assigned to Ranch. While in team, Elizabee's stats will be increased.
partnerSkill.name: Worker Bee

title: Guardian Commander

description: A chosen queen to rule over Beegardes. There is a never ending stream of servants willing to work themselves to death for the pleasure of serving their queen.
name: Elizabee

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, stats will increase the more Beegarde are in your team.
partnerSkill.name: Queen Bee Command

title: Empress of the Hive

description: Grintale's eyes light up the moment anyone enters its territory. This is no figure of speechits eyes literally light up.
name: Grintale

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Neutral attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Plump Body

title: Marshmallow Body

description: Crawling along the ground, it eats microscopic organic matter. After a while, it discharges any substances that provide no nutrition. By using it as a mop for cleaning, everyone wins!
name: Swee

partnerSkill.description: While in team, Sweepa's stats will be increased.
partnerSkill.name: Fluffy

title: Curious Floof

description: While hibernating, a large number of Swee hide within its voluminous body hair. The most ever recorded is 101.
name: Sweepa

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While fighting together, stats will increase the more Swee are in your team.
partnerSkill.name: King of Fluff

title: Majesty of Fuzz

description: It can curl up its body and roll around at extremely high speeds. Long ago, people would tie bags of milk to domesticated Chillet as they grazed to produce butter using this spinning force.
name: Chillet

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Dragon damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Wriggling Weasel

title: Dancer on the Plains

description: It used to be considered an emissary of the Thunder God, and thus was not hunted by people. However, after witnesses observed one die from a lightning strike, its reverence faded, and it quite literally fell into the role of a workhorse.
name: Univolt

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Electric damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Swift Deity

title: Swift Deity

description: On nights when the aurora is visible, it looks up towards the sky and begins to howl a beautiful song. This does, however, leave it vulnerable to attacks from enemies.
name: Foxcicle

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Ice Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Aurora Guide

title: Claws of Ice

description: Its entire body has evolved into a highly efficient radiator, gifting it with astounding stamina. When someone has mounted it, this Pal takes caution not to burn them.
name: Pyrin

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Fire damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Red Hare

title: Steed of Flames

description: It burns mysterious dark matter as energy and expels the remaining particles from its body. If someone rides it, they should take care so as not to gallop down the path of darkness.
name: Pyrin Noct

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Black Hare

title: Steed of Darkness

description: Its transparent cerulean antlers glow with the cold of absolute zero. Any who touch them with their bare hands are instantly frozen over and smashed to pieces.
name: Reindrix

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Keeps the rider cool in hot environments.
partnerSkill.name: Cool Body

title: Beast of Blizzards

description: At full speed, it could be mistaken for a bolt of lightning. If two Rayhounds collide, the sound is like that of a powerful thunderclap.
name: Rayhound

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can double jump while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Jumping Force

title: Electro-charged Zoomies

description: Despite its appearance, Kitsun is extremely sensitive and will flee into a cave when spooked. Long ago, it was considered an ill omen if one were found nearby.
name: Kitsun

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Unaffected by the cold or heat while riding this Pal.
partnerSkill.name: Clear Mind

title: Guardian of the Azure Flame

description: Often kind to lonely pals. However, the moment a Pal mistakes this for actual companionship, it seizes the opportunity to blast them with a thunderbolt.
name: Dazzi

partnerSkill.description: While in team, appears near the player. Follows up player attacks with lightning bolts.
partnerSkill.name: Lady of Lightning

title: Born of the Storm

description: It can control those who carelessly stare into its eyes. Those seen with a Lunaris are in its mind, simply under its control.
name: Lunaris

partnerSkill.description: While in team, Lunaris manipulates gravity, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: Antigravity

title: Extraterrestrial

description: A Pal who once angered cannot be pacified. It rages on and on like an inferno. The phrase |step on a Dinossom's tail| has come to mean enraging someone.
name: Dinossom

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Grass attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Fragrant Dragon

title: Guardian of Blossoming Gardens

description: Though struck by lightning, it lives on. The phrase |struck by a Dinossom Lux's bolt| has come to mean narrowly escaping death.
name: Dinossom Lux

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Electric attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Thunder Dragon

title: Guardian of Lightning

description: Its hydrodynamic form is well suited to life in water. Poachers often catch them and use them in place of surfboards.
name: Surfent

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden to travel on water. While mounted, prevents stamina depletion while moving over water.
partnerSkill.name: Swift Swimmer

title: The Ocean's Wrath

description: Its aerodynamic form is well suited to life on the sand. Poachers often catch them and use them in place of surfboards.
name: Surfent Terra

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden.
partnerSkill.name: Sand Swimmer

title: The Desert's Wrath

description: It relishes the peculiar scent living things give off when they are near death. If a Maraith has taken a liking to you, it is safe to assume that is why.
name: Maraith

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Messenger of Death

title: Messenger of Death

description: A walking contradiction, possessing the strongest shell and the only drill capable of piercing it. |Digtoise's Fable| is a popular children's tale.
name: Digtoise

partnerSkill.description: When activated, performs Shell Spin, follows the player while spinning, and mines ores efficiently.
partnerSkill.name: Drill Crusher

title: Drilling Machine

description: Often appears out of the blue to flaunt its prized wings in front of other Pals. Although this appears to be an intimidation tactic, the Pal seems to derive some kind of pleasure from the display.
name: Tombat

partnerSkill.description: When activated, uses ultrasonic waves to detect the location of nearby Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Ultrasonic Sensor

title: Trickster

description: Seeking a night of love, it is always chasing someone around. At first it only showed interest in other Pals, but in recent years even humans have become the target of its debauchery.
name: Lovander

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, grants the player and Lovander the life steal effect which absorbs some of the received damage and restores Health.
partnerSkill.name: Heart Drain

title: Pal on the Prowl

description: When it starts crying, this Pal produces magma in place of tears. The magma that pours out is absorbed back into its body, causing it to get hotter and hotter. The more it cries, the stronger it becomes.
name: Flambelle

partnerSkill.description: Sometimes produces Flame Organ when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Magma Tears

title: Molten Daughter

description: The melodies of a flute made from the exoskeleton of a Vanwyrm are said to cross whole mountain ranges. In ages past, such flutes were used to signal an attack.
name: Vanwyrm

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Increases damage player deals to enemy weak points while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Aerial Marauder

title: Aerial Marauder

description: The melodies of a flute made from the exoskeleton of a Vanwyrm Cryst are said to cross whole mountain ranges. In ages past, such flutes were used to signal victory in battle.
name: Vanwyrm Cryst

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Increases damage player deals to enemy weak points while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Aerial Marauder

title: Marauder of Frozen Skies

description: Its body becomes a blade upon death, to be taken up by the next generation. If someone other than a Bushi wields this blade, the soul within torments them until they are driven mad.
name: Bushi

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Iaigiri.
partnerSkill.name: Brandish Blade

title: Vagrant Warrior

description: Some think it is a related species to Ragnahawk, but there is in fact no connection. Using its sharp beak, it descends on its prey in a quick motion that resembles a bolt of lightning.
name: Beakon

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Applies Electric damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Thunderous

title: Wings of Thunder

description: Some think it is a related species to Beakon, but there is in fact no connection. It mainly eats rocks, and after many long years its beak and head have hardened to accommodate this diet.
name: Ragnahawk

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Applies Fire damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Flame Wing

title: Wings of Inferno

description: With the power of shadows, it produces arcane phenomena. It prefers to eat food raw and is particularly hostile towards Wixen.
name: Katress

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Neutral Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Grimoire Collector

title: Phantasmal Feline

description: With the power of light, it produces arcane phenomena. It prefers to eat food well-done and is particularly hostile towards Katress.
name: Wixen

partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, applies Fire damage to the player's attacks.
partnerSkill.name: Lord Fox

title: Fire Licked Furball

description: Land that Verdash has run across becomes extremely fertile, with thick vegetation growing there soon after. It will not run anywhere that herbicide has been used.
name: Verdash

partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases player's movement speed and applies Grass damage to the player's attacks.
partnerSkill.name: Grassland Speedster

title: Gale of the Forest

description: The castle was filled with the king's favorite flowers. A great battle ensued, and flames approached the castle. Amidst the chaos, the spirit of a flower appeared. - From the fairy tale, |The King's Flower.|
name: Vaelet

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Ground Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Purification of Gaia

title: Voice of the Violets

description: A Pal that likes the rain, and will often bask in rain showers until the weather clears up. On rainy days, Foxparks can often be found taking shelter beneath it.
name: Sibelyx

partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Blizzard Spike. Sometimes produces High Quality Cloth when assigned to Ranch.
partnerSkill.name: Silk Maker

title: Pallid Lady

description: It possesses a demeanor as pure as its appearance suggests. Perhaps because of this, it is sometimes unable to discern good from evil, often allowing wrongdoers to take advantage of it.
name: Elphidran

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. While fighting together, Dark Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Amicable Holy Dragon

title: Gentle Sky Dragon

description: It possesses a demeanor as pure as its appearance suggests. Perhaps because of this, it harbors no ill will in any of its actions and is indifferent even after killing someone.
name: Elphidran Aqua

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. While fighting together, Fire Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Amicable Water Dragon

title: Beast of the Tides

description: Its personality changes depending on the quality of the water it was born into. Kelpsea born into polluted waters are generally ill-tempered and quickly become delinquents.
name: Kelpsea

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Water Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Aqua Spout

title: Child of the Deep

description: Their personalities change depending on the temperature of the water where they were born. Kelpsea born in warm waters generally have a passionate, motivated personality.
name: Kelpsea Ignis

partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Fire Pals.
partnerSkill.name: Lava Spout

title: Child of Molten Depths

description: This Pal's white ribbon turns black if doused with impure water. Given its usefulness in detecting poison, this Pal was once overhunted. This past has left them bitter towards humanity.
name: Azurobe

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden to travel on water. Applies Water damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Waterwing Dance

title: Lady of the Lake

description: It can easily climb steep mountains with its hard claws. However, its short legs make it difficult to descend, often leaving it stranded in high places.
name: Cryolinx

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Dragon Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Dragon Hunter

title: Predator of Snowy Peaks

description: While it prefers raw meat, it always ends up eating well-done meat. This is due to its blistering claws, which it uses as its weaponit simply doesn't realize its prey gets burned to a crisp.
name: Blazehowl

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While fighting together, Grass Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Hellflame Lion

title: Crimson Goliath

description: While it prefers raw meat, it always ends up eating tainted meat. This is due to its dark claws, which it uses as its weaponit simply doesn't realize its prey gets cursed.
name: Blazehowl Noct

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While fighting together, Neutral Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Darkflame Lion

title: Inferno Goliath

description: Contrary to its blas appearance, it's quite ferocious. It perceives everything in its sight as prey and will stop at nothing to devour it.
name: Relaxaurus

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a missile launcher while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Hungry Missile

title: Gluttonous Dragon

description: One day, Relaxaurus had an idea. Maybe it was about time for a change. Just then, an electric shock raced through its body!
name: Relaxaurus Lux

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a missile launcher while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Missile Party

title: Gluttonous Thunder Dragon

description: Its scent drastically changes before and after pairing. It exudes a pleasing aroma after finding a partner, which is called the |fragrance of first love.|
name: Broncherry

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Broncherry helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: Overaffectionate

title: Winds of Spring

description: Its scent drastically changes before and after pairing. It exudes a pleasing aroma before finding a partner, which is called the |perfume of purity.|
name: Broncherry Aqua

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Broncherry Aqua helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: Overaffectionate

title: Waves of Summer

description: A Pal that transforms into a massive plant when at the end of its life. Once every ten years, a beautiful flower blooms and a new Petallia is born.
name: Petallia

partnerSkill.description: When activated, uses medicinal flowers to restore the player's Health.
partnerSkill.name: Blessing of the Flower Spirit

title: Lady of the Garden

description: Magma-like blood runs throughout its body. If a large amount of water is thrown on it, this water rapidly heats, causing an immense vapor explosion.
name: Reptyro

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of mining ores while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Ore-loving Beast

title: Magma-born Juggernaut

description: Ice cold blood runs throughout its body. If heated rapidly, its blood evaporates, causing an immense vapor explosion.
name: Reptyro Cryst

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of mining ores while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Ice-loving Beast

title: Ice-breaking Juggernaut

description: Melpaca serve this Pal. Contests between Kingpaca offer up their vassals as a wager. Those seen alone are losers of such contests.
name: Kingpaca

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Kingpaca helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: King of Muscles

title: Supreme Fluff Commander

description: With a heart of ice, this Pal is terrible at expressing its emotions. A solitary individual is pitiable, seen as too clumsy in the eyes of a Melpaca.
name: Kingpaca Cryst

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Kingpaca Cryst helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: King of Muscles

title: Azure Fluff Commander

description: The vegetation on its back varies between individuals. There is a long history of appreciating this veritable garden of a Pal, and there are even Mammorest pruning specialists.
name: Mammorest

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of cutting trees and mining ores while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Gaia Crusher

title: King of the Forest

description: The vegetation on its back varies from individual to individual. There was a time when seeds of presumed extinct plants were found still frozen on the back of a Mammorest Cryst.
name: Mammorest Cryst

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of cutting trees and mining ores while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Ice Crusher

title: Frozen King

description: Researchers once tried to shave off its hair to reveal its true form. In the end, only hair was left, as if that was all there was to begin with.
name: Wumpo

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Wumpo helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Snowy Mountain

title: Guardian of the Snowy Mountain

description: Researchers once tried to cut the grass off its body to reveal its true form. In the end, only grass was left, as if that was all there was to begin with.
name: Wumpo Botan

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Wumpo Botan helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.
partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Grassy Fields

title: Guardian of the Grassy Fields

description: The ultra-hard armor surrounding its body is extremely strong and heat resistant. Even a napalm blast would hardly leave a scratch.
name: Warsect

partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases player's defense and reduces damage received from Fire.
partnerSkill.name: Hard Armor

title: Unyielding Colossus

description: In ages past, its beautiful visage was a common sight in paintings. As time passed, its beautiful pelt and antlers were often seen in works of art.
name: Fenglope

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can double jump while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Wind and Clouds

title: Drifting Cloud

description: Attacking from the shadows, this Pal traps its prey within its cloak-like wings. It's probably best not to know what happens within them, or why the inside of its wings are stained red.
name: Felbat

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, grants the player and Felbat the life steal effect which absorbs some of the received damage and restores Health.
partnerSkill.name: Life Steal

title: Gloom-shrouded Bloodsucker

description: Sleeping while cuddling a Quivern is said to be a heavenly experience, but there are some who have been crushed and sent to heaven by ones that toss and turn in their sleep.
name: Quivern

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Enhances Dragon attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Sky Dragon's Affection

title: Wings of White

description: Legends say it was born during a volcanic eruption. A strange group even claims that this continent is laid upon the back of a giant Blazamut.
name: Blazamut

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Fire attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Magma Kaiser

title: Cursed Tyrant

description: It calls forth lightning from the depths of hell. One who dies from Helzephyr's inferno is sure to be sent to the underworld.
name: Helzephyr

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Wings of Death

title: Wings of Death

description: A savage beast born of the abyss. Thou shall not stand before the beast. Thou shall not heed the beast.
name: Astegon

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Increases damage dealt to ore while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Black Anklyosaur

title: Ravager of Stars

description: Being made of pure energy, its insides are completely hollow. This Pal crams still-living prey into its hollow body, where it absorbs them. Hellish screams of pain can often be heard coming from inside this Pal.
name: Menasting

partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases the player's defense and Electric Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Steel Scorpion

title: Unstoppable Stinger

description: Once seen as a symbol of nobility, and an idol for those who shunned wealth and power. Yet over time, this Pal became a token of death.
name: Anubis

partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, applies Ground damage to the player's attacks. Sometimes dodges attacks with a high speed sidestep while in battle.
partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Desert

title: Guardian of the Dark Sun

description: Legend says that the Jormuntide was once a wise man, who after being wrongly convicted and cast into a whirlpool, returned as this Pal to destroy those who wronged him.
name: Jormuntide

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden to travel on water. While mounted, prevents stamina depletion while moving over water.
partnerSkill.name: Stormbringer Sea Dragon

title: Emperor of the Sea

description: Legend says the Jormuntide Ignis was once a warrior who, after being wrongly convicted and cast into a volcano, returned as this Pal to destroy those who wronged him.
name: Jormuntide Ignis

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Fire attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Stormbringer Lava Dragon

title: Volcanic Emperor

description: It was once believed to usher in the dry season. Whenever there was a drought the previous year, people would relentlessly seek to cull its numbers, hoping to bring about a plentiful harvest in the next year.
name: Suzaku

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Enhances Fire attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Wings of Flame

title: Ruler of the Crimson Dawn

description: It was once believed to usher in the rainy season. If there was a flood the previous year, people would relentlessly seek to cull its numbers, hoping to avert disaster in the coming year.
name: Suzaku Aqua

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Enhances Water attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Wings of Water

title: Ruler of the Cobalt Dusk

description: With a friendly smile and a hardy physique, it is docile towards one it recognizes as a partner. For reasons unexplained, its personality undergoes a drastic change when wielding a minigun.
name: Grizzbolt

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a minigun while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Yellow Tank

title: Claws of Lightning

description: A docile Pal full of love. It watches over small Pals who have lost their parents. It uses a full-power Solar Blast to discipline naughty Pals.
name: Lyleen

partnerSkill.description: When activated, the queen's soothing graces greatly restore the player's Health.
partnerSkill.name: Harvest Goddess

title: Lily Empress

description: An elegant Pal full of grace. It admonishes any who are disrespectful with a painful slap. Some Pals actively seek out this punishment.
name: Lyleen Noct

partnerSkill.description: When activated, the queen's soothing graces greatly restore the player's Health.
partnerSkill.name: Goddess of the Tranquil Light

title: Empress of the Abyss

description: When it finds its prey it unleashes a whirlwind of flames, burning the entire area to ash. Faleris breath is known for its pleasing scent.
name: Faleris

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. While fighting together, Ice Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Scorching Predator

title: Sentinel of Dawn

description: It sends electricity into its foes' wounds, roasting them from the inside out. Fights between Orserk end in the blink of an eye.
name: Orserk

partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Water Pals drop more items when defeated.
partnerSkill.name: Ferocious Thunder Dragon

title: Roaring Thunder

description: Born from the depths of insanity, its very existence should not be. Having lost all genetic ties to other Pals, one wonders if it could still even be considered a Pal.
name: Shadowbeak

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Enhances Dark attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Modified DNA

title: Unknown Life Form

description: Once one with Necromus. Its gleaming form is free of all negative emotions. However, a glimmer of hatred can still be seen deep within its eyes.
name: Paladius

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can triple jump while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Holy Knight of the Firmament

title: Holy Knight of Legend

description: Once one with Paladius. Its darkened form is the embodiment of negative emotions. However, a glimmer of compassion can still be seen deep within its eyes.
name: Necromus

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can double jump while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Dark Knight of the Abyss

title: Dark Knight of Legend

description: Guardian deity of Palpagos Island, known as the Winter Caller. In the past, when a calamity struck the land, it soared into the sky and sealed away the threat by casting the island into an eternal winter.
name: Frostallion

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Changes the player's attack type to Ice and enhances Ice attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Ice Steed

title: Legendary Steed of Ice

description: Guardian deity of Palpagos Island known as the Night Caller. In the past, when a calamity struck the land, it soared into the sky and sealed away the threat by casting the island into eternal darkness.
name: Frostallion Noct

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Changes the player's attack type to Dark and enhances Dark attacks while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Black Steed

title: Legendary Steed of Darkness

description: Watches over Palpagos Island from high above. When calamity returns to the land, the earth will split open, and the skies will burn. It is destined to strike down the calamity in a flash of total destruction.
name: Jetragon

partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Can rapidly fire a missile launcher while mounted.
partnerSkill.name: Aerial Missile

title: Legendary Celestial Dragon
